# 💍 Wedding Studio — Page Creator

A drag-and-drop wedding website creator that stores page structure in **Firebase Firestore** and hosts images via **Google Drive**. Built as a static site deployable to **GitHub Pages** — no server required.

---

## ✨ Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| 🎨 Drag & Drop Editor | Blocks similar to WordPress Gutenberg |
| 🎠 Carousel | Auto-playing image slideshow |
| ⏱️ Countdown | Live countdown to the wedding day |
| 📋 Details | Venue, date, dress code cards |
| 📬 RSVP Form | Stores responses in Firestore |
| 🖼️ Gallery | Masonry-style photo grid |
| 🎨 Theme Editor | Colors, fonts, preset palettes |
| 🔐 Google Sign-In | Firebase Authentication |
| 📱 Responsive | Mobile-friendly viewer |

---

## 🚀 Setup Guide

### Step 1 — Create a Firebase Project

1. Go to [console.firebase.google.com](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Click **Add project** → name it (e.g. `wedding-studio`)
3. Disable Google Analytics (optional) → **Create project**

### Step 2 — Enable Firestore

1. In Firebase Console → **Build → Firestore Database**
2. Click **Create database** → choose **Start in test mode**
3. Select a region → **Done**

> **Test mode** lets anyone read/write for 30 days. Before going live, update the Firestore rules:
> ```
> rules_version = '2';
> service cloud.firestore {
>   match /databases/{database}/documents {
>     match /weddings/{weddingId} {
>       allow read: if true;
>       allow write: if request.auth != null && resource.data.ownerId == request.auth.uid;
>       allow create: if request.auth != null;
>       match /rsvps/{rsvpId} {
>         allow read: if request.auth != null;
>         allow create: if true;
>       }
>     }
>   }
> }
> ```

### Step 3 — Enable Google Authentication

1. Firebase Console → **Build → Authentication**
2. Click **Get started** → **Sign-in method**
3. Enable **Google** → set project support email → **Save**

### Step 4 — Get Your Firebase Config

1. Firebase Console → **Project settings** (gear icon)
2. Under **Your apps** → click the `</>` web icon → register app
3. Copy the `firebaseConfig` object

### Step 5 — Add Authorized Domains

1. Firebase Console → **Authentication → Settings → Authorized domains**
2. Add: `YOUR_USERNAME.github.io`
3. Also add `localhost` for local testing

### Step 6 — Configure the App

Open `config.js` and fill in your Firebase credentials:

```javascript
const FIREBASE_CONFIG = {
  apiKey:            "YOUR_FIREBASE_API_KEY",
  authDomain:        "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.firebaseapp.com",
  projectId:         "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
  storageBucket:     "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.appspot.com",
  messagingSenderId: "YOUR_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID",
  appId:             "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
```

---

## 🚢 Deploy to GitHub Pages

```bash
# 1. Create a new GitHub repository
# 2. Clone it and copy your files in:
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
cp wedding-creator/* YOUR_REPO/

# 3. Push to GitHub
cd YOUR_REPO
git add .
git commit -m "Initial deploy"
git push origin main

# 4. Enable GitHub Pages
# GitHub → Repository → Settings → Pages → Source: "main" branch
```

Your site will be live at:
`https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/YOUR_REPO/`

---

## 📸 Using Google Drive for Images

1. Upload your image to Google Drive
2. Right-click → **Share** → **Anyone with the link** → Copy link
3. Paste the URL into the editor's image field

The app automatically converts:
```
https://drive.google.com/file/d/ABC123/view?usp=sharing
                    ↓
https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/ABC123
```

> **Tip:** Make sure the image is shared as "Anyone with the link can view"

---

## 🖥️ Usage

### Viewing a Wedding Page

```
https://your-site.github.io/?weddingId=Andrea+Kylie
```

The `weddingId` is the ID you chose when creating the wedding in the editor (e.g., `Andrea+Kylie`).

### Editing a Wedding Page

```
https://your-site.github.io/editor.html
```

1. Sign in with Google
2. Select an existing wedding or create a new one
3. Drag blocks from the left panel to the canvas
4. Click a block to edit its properties
5. Change colors & fonts via 🎨 Theme
6. Press **Save** or `Ctrl+S`

---

## ⌨️ Keyboard Shortcuts

| Shortcut | Action |
|---|---|
| `Ctrl+S` / `⌘S` | Save |
| `Escape` | Deselect block |
| `Delete` | Remove selected block |

