## 🗂️ File Structure

```
/
├── index.html      # Wedding page viewer (public-facing)
├── editor.html     # Drag-and-drop page editor
├── config.js       # Firebase configuration (edit this!)
└── README.md       # This file
```

---

## 🧩 Block Types

| Block | Description |
|---|---|
| **Hero** | Full-screen header with couple names, date, background image |
| **Text** | Heading + paragraph, with alignment and size options |
| **Image** | Single photo from Google Drive |
| **Carousel** | Auto-playing slideshow of multiple photos |
| **Countdown** | Live days/hours/minutes/seconds counter |
| **Details** | Icon cards for date, venue, dress code etc. |
| **RSVP** | Guest response form stored in Firestore |
| **Gallery** | 2–4 column photo grid with lightbox |
| **Divider** | Decorative section separator (line, floral, dots, wave) |
| **Quote** | Styled pull-quote with attribution |

---

## 🛟 Troubleshooting

| Problem | Solution |
|---|---|
| Sign-in fails | Check your domain is in Firebase Authorized Domains |
| Images don't load | Make sure Google Drive files are shared "Anyone with link" |
| Save fails | Check Firestore security rules allow your user to write |
| Viewer shows "Not Found" | Check spelling of `weddingId` in the URL matches exactly |
| CORS errors locally | Use a local server: `npx serve .` or `python -m http.server` |

